The '''ASU Soccer Stadium''' is a [[soccer-specific stadium]] in [[Boone, North Carolina]] and is home to the [[Appalachian State Mountaineers]] men's and women's [[soccer]] teams. The stadium, which is part of the Ted Mackorell Soccer Complex, opened for its first game in 2008 against the [[College of Charleston]] Cougars.<ref>{{cite news|title=Mountaineers Roll in SoCon Opener 3-0 Over College of Charleston|author=Appalachian Sports Information|publisher=GoASU|date=2008-10-01|url=http://www.goasu.com/ViewArticle.dbml?SPSID=106985&SPID=13258&DB_OEM_ID=21500&ATCLID=1594562}}</ref>
The stadium is a replacement for the old ASU Soccer Stadium, which was opened in 2005.
