'''Bob Holtzman''' (born 1972) is a [[List of television reporters|television bureau-reporter]] for [[ESPN]] located in the city of [[Cincinnati, Ohio]]. He contributes to stories on ESPN shows such as ''[[SportsCenter]]'',<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://brownscountry.com/2012/04/26/live-draft-day/|title=Live Draft Day|last=Crookston|first=Jeremy|date=April 26, 2012|website=brownscountry.com|publisher=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140512221521/http://brownscountry.com/2012/04/26/live-draft-day/|archive-date=May 12, 2014|access-date=2016-07-08}}</ref> ''[[Outside the Lines]]'',<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/page2/tvlistings/show70transcript.html|title=ESPN.com - Page2 - Outside the Lines: What's The Deal?|website=espn.go.com|access-date=2016-07-08}}</ref> ''[[Sunday NFL Countdown]]'',<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://frontrow.espn.go.com/2012/01/inside-the-making-of-espn%E2%80%99s-sunday-nfl-countdown-part-i/|title=Inside the making of ESPN’s Sunday NFL Countdown: Part I|last=Nwulu|first=Mac|date=January 20, 2012|website=espn.go.com|publisher=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120126183401/http://frontrow.espn.go.com/2012/01/inside-the-making-of-espn%E2%80%99s-sunday-nfl-countdown-part-i/|dead-url=yes|archive-date=January 26, 2012|access-date=2016-07-08}}</ref> and ''[[Baseball Tonight]]''.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |url=http://www.espnmediazone3.com/us/2010/03/27/holtzman_bob/ |title=Reflections on NFL, ESPN, FinishLine.com and The New York Giants |website=www.espnmediazone3.com |access-date=2016-07-08 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120716041739/http://www.espnmediazone3.com/us/2010/03/27/holtzman_bob/ |archivedate=2012-07-16 |df= }}</ref>
Before joining [[ESPN]] in November 2000, he was a reporter at [[WCPO]] in [[Cincinnati, Ohio]] from 1996 to 2000.<ref name=":0" /> Prior to that, he served in a similar role at [[KCRA]] in [[Sacramento, California]] and [[KRQE]] in [[Albuquerque, New Mexico]].<ref name=":0" />
Holtzman is a 1993 graduate of the [[University of Kansas]] with a degrees in journalism and psychology.<ref name=":0" /> He is also a certified meteorologist.
Holtzman was born in [[Tulsa, Oklahoma]], but grew up in [[San Diego, California]]. He currently resides near [[Florence, Kentucky]].
