{{infobox country at games | NOC = SEY | NOCname = [[Seychelles Olympic and Commonwealth Games Association]] | games = Olympics | year = | flagcaption = [[Flag of the Seychelles]] | oldcode = | website = | location = | competitors = | sports = | flagbearer = | rank = | gold = 0 | silver = 0 | bronze = 0 | officials = | appearances = | app_begin_year = | app_end_year = | summerappearances = {{Team appearances list|team=Seychelles|competition=Summer Olympics|begin_year=|end_year= }} | winterappearances = | seealso = }} '''[[Seychelles]]''' first participated at the '''[[Olympic Games]]''' in 1980, and has sent athletes to compete in most [[Summer Olympic Games]] since then, missing only the [[1988 Summer Olympics|1988 Games]] when Seychelles did not respond to the invitation sent by the [[International Olympic Committee|IOC]].<ref name="FindlingPelle1996">{{cite book|author1=John E. Findling|author2=Kimberly D. Pelle|title=Historical Dictionary of the Modern Olympic Movement|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=vj5-Srq3ki4C&pg=PA182|year=1996|publisher=Greenwood Publishing Group|isbn=978-0-313-28477-9|pages=182–}}</ref> The nation has never participated in the [[Winter Olympic Games]].
To date, no Seychellois athlete has ever won an Olympic medal.
The [[National Olympic Committee]] for Seychelles was created in 1979 and recognized by the [[International Olympic Committee]] that same year.
